Via Twitter Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Lagos - Amnesty International (AI) has released a video to back its report that Nigerian security forces killed at least 150 peaceful protesters in a "chilling campaign" to repress renewed demands to create a breakaway state of Biafra in the southeast.&nbsp;Nigeria's military, however, denied "killing of defenceless agitators".&nbsp;According to AI, an analysis of 87 videos, 122 photographs and 146 testimonies showed "the military fired live ammunition with little or no warning" into crowds protesting between August 2015 and August 2016".&nbsp;Watch the video below.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.